00:09:47.340 --> 00:09:52.710
the electric field propagating
at angular frequency omega,

00:09:52.710 --> 00:10:00.580
with a wave number k, going
toward positive z direction.

00:10:00.580 --> 00:10:04.180
And the electric field is
perpendicular to the direction

00:10:04.180 --> 00:10:08.500
of propagation in
the x direction.

00:10:08.500 --> 00:10:14.410
And also, this electric
field have a phase of phi 1.

00:10:14.410 --> 00:10:18.310
So that's actually what
we know already by now.

00:10:18.310 --> 00:10:20.710
What does this mean,
this expression mean?

00:10:20.710 --> 00:10:25.540
And it's actually the harmonic
oscillating electric field.

00:10:25.540 --> 00:10:28.960
And of course, since I am
talking about interference,

00:10:28.960 --> 00:10:34.990
basically, I can add this,
the first electric field

00:10:34.990 --> 00:10:37.660
and the second
electric field together

00:10:37.660 --> 00:10:39.020
and see what will happen.

00:10:39.020 --> 00:10:42.300
So now, if you define
the second electric field

00:10:42.300 --> 00:10:46.615
to be A2, which is the
amplitude, cosine omega

00:10:46.615 --> 00:10:52.630
t minus kz, basically, they have
the same wavelengths and also

00:10:52.630 --> 00:10:54.810
the angular frequency--

00:10:54.810 --> 00:10:57.130
plus phi 2.

00:10:57.130 --> 00:10:59.710
But they have different phase.

00:10:59.710 --> 00:11:02.650
And of course, in
this setup, I asked

00:11:02.650 --> 00:11:05.140
