the same direction, which

00:11:05.140 --> 00:11:07.240
is the x direction.

00:11:07.240 --> 00:11:08.920
So we were wondering,
what is going

00:11:08.920 --> 00:11:15.510
to happen if I consider the
superposition of these two

00:11:15.510 --> 00:11:18.600
electric fields.

00:11:18.600 --> 00:11:22.900
And the total electric field,
which is called the E vector,

00:11:22.900 --> 00:11:26.110
is actually E1 plus E2.

00:11:29.380 --> 00:11:31.810
So before that, I would
like to remind you

00:11:31.810 --> 00:11:37.970
about pointing vector and
also the so-called intensity.

00:11:37.970 --> 00:11:40.510
So pointing factor
is actually defined

00:11:40.510 --> 00:11:43.300
as this S vector,
pointing vector,

00:11:43.300 --> 00:11:51.370
is equal to 1 over mu 0 E
cross B. So this is actually

00:11:51.370 --> 00:11:56.290
the directional flux of
energy per unit area.

00:11:56.290 --> 00:12:00.520
So that should be the
pointing vector which

00:12:00.520 --> 00:12:03.720
we have been using for a while.

00:12:03.720 --> 00:12:09.630
And also, another reminder is
that, given the electric field,

00:12:09.630 --> 00:12:13.780
which is actually a
harmonic progressing wave,

00:12:13.780 --> 00:12:16.750
the corresponding
B field would be

00:12:16.750 --> 00:12:23.800
equal to 1/v. v is actually
the speed of the light

00:12:23.800 --> 00:12:26.800
in some specific material.

00:12:26.800 --> 00:12:30.180
And k hat is actually
the direction

00:12:30.180 --> 00:12:35.940
of propagation across
E. This will give you

00:12:35.940 --> 00:12:38.260
the magnitude and
also the direction

00:12:38.260 --> 00:12:42.100
of the corresponding
magnetic field

00:12:42.100 --> 00:12:46.720
for the electromagnetic waves.

00:12:46.720 --> 00:12:49.750
So now I'm interested
in what would

00:12:49.750 --> 00:12:59.770
be the resulting intensity, I,
if I try to superimpose this,

00:12:59.770 --> 00:13:05.140
to try to put together
these two electric fields.

00:13:05.140 --> 00:13:08.200
As you can see, these
two electric field

00:13:08.200 --> 00:13:09.370
have different phase.

00:13:09.370 --> 00:13:11.140
The first one has phase phi 1.

00:13:11.140 --> 00:13:14.270
The second one, has phase phi 2.

00:13:14.270 --> 00:13:18.920
So this means that they
may reach maxima or minima

00:13:18.920 --> 00:13:23.000
at different position in space.

00:13:23.000 --> 00:13:25.970
In this case, it's
in the z direction.

00:13:25.970 --> 00:13:33.710
And what I'm actually defining
here is two plane waves.

00:13:33.710 --> 00:13:37.020
And so it really
depends on what would

00:13:37.020 --> 00:13:41.230
be the relative phase
for the first and second

00:13:41.230 --> 00:13:43.490
electromagnetic wave.

00:13:43.490 --> 00:13:48.920
In order to quantify how
much they cancel each other

00:13:48.920 --> 00:13:53.000
or how much they enhance each
other, what I'm going to do

00:13:53.000 --> 00:13:58.670
is to evaluate the
intensity of the resulting

00:13:58.670 --> 00:14:00.470
electromagnetic waves.

00:14:00.470 --> 00:14:02.210
And what is actually intensity?

00:14:02.210 --> 00:14:05.310
Intensity is actually
the amplitude

00:14:05.310 --> 00:14:07.490
of the pointing vector.

00:14:07.490 --> 00:14:14.170
So I write this as the length of
the S vector, pointing vector.

00:14:14.170 --> 00:14:19.010
And I can, of course, calculate
what will be the value of this

00:14:19.010 --> 00:14:21.440
or, say, the length of
the pointing vector.

00:14:21.440 --> 00:14:24.530
This will be equal
to 1 over mu 0,

00:14:24.530 --> 00:14:26.630
based on these equations here--

00:14:26.630 --> 00:14:27.770
just a reminder.

00:14:27.770 --> 00:14:32.160
And I would like to know what
would be the length of the E

00:14:32.160 --> 00:14:35.030
cross B field.

00:14:35.030 --> 00:14:38.600
That will give you the length
of the pointing vector.

00:14:38.600 --> 00:14:47.900
And basically, what you're going
to get is 1 over mu 0 times--

00:14:47.900 --> 00:14:52.790
since the B field is
actually highly related

00:14:52.790 --> 00:14:59.780
to the electric field, and
it takes a hit of 1/v, right,

00:14:59.780 --> 00:15:01.670
in terms of the size
of the amplitude.

00:15:01.670 --> 00:15:08.430
So basically, you're going
to get 1/v, E squared.

00:15:12.280 --> 00:15:16.420
And this cross product
actually is OK,

00:15:16.420 --> 00:15:21.550
because it become E squared,
because B field and the E field

00:15:21.550 --> 00:15:24.930
are always orthogonal
to each other.

00:15:24.930 --> 00:15:28.140
And I can now rewrite
this v. v is actually

00:15:28.140 --> 00:15:32.830
the velocity of the
speed of light in matter.

00:15:32.830 --> 00:15:35.120
So basically, what
I can rewrite is

00:15:35.120 --> 00:15:42.790
that will become
1/v will become c/n,

00:15:42.790 --> 00:15:49.060
which is actually the refractive
index of a specific material.

00:15:49.060 --> 00:15:52.560
And still I have E squared here.

00:15:52.560 --> 00:15:56.320
Finally, I can
rewrite this formula,

00:15:56.320 --> 00:16:05.320
since c is equal to 1 over
square root mu 0 epsilon 0.

00:16:05.320 --> 00:16:09.030
Therefore, I can
rewrite this expression

00:16:09.030 --> 00:16:11.210
in terms of epsilon 0.

00:16:11.210 --> 00:16:16.190
And what I'm going to get
is c times n time epsilon 0,

00:16:16.190 --> 00:16:19.120
There E squared.

00:16:19.120 --> 00:16:25.570
So basically, what I do is
I multiply both numerator

00:16:25.570 --> 00:16:33.490
and the denominator
by c, and also

00:16:33.490 --> 00:16:35.560
I actually use this expression.

00:16:35.560 --> 00:16:37.990
Then I can actually
cancel the mu 0

00:16:37.990 --> 00:16:44.380
and then write everything in
terms of c, n, and epsilon 0.

00:16:44.380 --> 00:16:47.750
So until here, there
was basically no magic.

00:16:47.750 --> 00:16:52.290
Basically, it's just
rewriting the length

00:16:52.290 --> 00:16:58.570
of the pointing vector
in terms of n and also

00:16:58.570 --> 00:17:01.640
the electric field.

00:17:01.640 --> 00:17:06.829
So now, what I am going to do
is to plug in this expression

00:17:06.829 --> 00:17:11.270
into that formula and see
what we are going to get.

00:17:11.270 --> 00:17:16.163
So let me evaluate what
would be the E squared,

00:17:16.163 --> 00:17:17.329
the length of the E squared.

00:17:17.329 --> 00:17:22.099
So basically, the definition
of the E is shown here.

00:17:22.099 --> 00:17:25.760
It's the superposition
of E1 and E2.

00:17:25.760 --> 00:17:28.910
Therefore, I can now
quickly write down

00:17:28.910 --> 00:17:31.430
what would be E squared here.

00:17:35.450 --> 00:17:42.140
Basically, you are going to
get A1 squared, cosine squared,

00:17:42.140 --> 00:17:47.660
omega t minus kz plus phi 1.

00:17:47.660 --> 00:17:53.300
